    <h4>Who has to Register for EPF</h4>
    <h6>To be eligible for PF Registration, an organization has to fulfill the following criteria:</h6>
    <ul class="a">
        <li>1.i.	A factory with the total employee strength of 20 or more.</li>
        <li>2.ii.	An establishment that employs more than 20 persons. Here, the Central Government defines the class of such firms.</li>
        <li>3.iii.	An establishment that has less than 20 workers and has been notified of compulsory registration for not less than 2 months.</li>
<li>iv.	Companies with less than 20 employees (Note: Such companies must issue a notice to the Employees’ Provident Fund Organization in 2 months or less than that)</li>
<li>v.	The employer and the employees of an establishment must mutually agree to apply for PF to the Central PF Commissioner. A notification has to be sent to the Official Gazette from the date of the agreement.</li>


    </ul>


<div>
     <h4>Documents Required for EPF Registration</h4>
<h6>1. Proprietorship Firm</h6>
<ul class="a">
<li>1. Name</li>
<li>2. PAN Card</li>
<li>3. ID Proof – Driving License / Passport / Voter Card</li>
<li>4. Address Proof for the premises</li>
<li>5. Residential address proof</li>
<li>6. Telephone number</li>



</ul>
</div>

<div>
     <h6>2. Society/Trust</h6>
<ul class="a">
    <li>1.	Certification of Incorporation</li>
<li>2.	MOA and By-laws</li>
<li>3.	Pan Card number</li>
<li>4.	Address proof</li>
<li>5.	ID proof</li>


</ul>
</div>

<div>
<h6>3. Partnership Firms</h6>
<ul class="a">
    <li>1. Certificate of Registration Firms</li>
<li>2. Partnership Deed</li>
<li>3.  ID Proof – Driving License / Passport / Voter Card</li>
<li>4. List of all partners with address proof</li>
<li>5. ID proof of all partners</li>

</ul>
</div>
<div>
<h6>4. LLP/Company</h6>
<ul class="a">
    <li>1. Incorporation Certificate</li>
<li>2.	proof of directors</li>
<li>3.	DSC of directors</li>
<li>4.	List of all directors with address proof </li>
<li>5.	ID proof</li>


</ul>
</div>
<div>
<h6>5. Employees</h6>
<ul class="a">
    <li>1.	Name</li>
<li>2.	Date of Joining</li>
<li>3.	Date of birth</li>
<li>4.	Mobile number</li>
<li>5.	Postal address</li>
<li>6. Name of Nominee</li>
<li>7.	Grade</li>
<li>8.	Salary</li>
<li>9.	Designation</li>
<li>10. ID Proof – Driving License / Passport / Voter Card</li>
<li>11. Bank account number with IFSC code</li>
<li>12. Voluntary application</li>
<li>13. Employee details</li>
<li>14. Signature</li>
<li>15. Date of agreement</li>

</ul>
</div>

<div>
<h6>6. Other Entities</h6>
<ul class="a">
    <li>1. First sale bill.</li>
<li>2. First purchase bill of raw material and machinery.</li>
<li>3. GST Registration Certificate, if registered</li>
<li>4. Bankers details- name, address, branch, IFSC code</li>
<li>5. Record of a monthly strength of the number of employees.</li>
<li>6. Register of salary and wages, all vouchers, all balance sheets from day one to current date of provisional coverage.</li>
<li>7. Salary and PF Statement.</li>
<li>8. Cross cancelled cheque.</li>


</ul>
